@wordwrap
@tab 8

@node sect0 "Name"
samdiskread, samdiskwrite - read or write an entire SAMDOS disk image 
@endnode

@node sect1 "Synopsis"
@{b}samdiskread@{ub} [ @{i}file@{ui} ] @{b}samdiskwrite@{ub} [ @{i}file@{ui} ] 


@endnode

@node sect2 "Description"
On a Sun SPARCstation, these programs configure the floppy disk device for SAMDOS format and then read or write an entire disk image.  On other workstations they do not perform configuration and are thus equivalent to a command such as @{b}dd bs=10240 count=80 .@{ub} @{i}Samdiskread@{ui} reads the floppy disk and writes it to the named file.  If no file is named then the output is produced on the standard output. 

@{i}Samdiskwrite@{ui} writes the contents of the named file on to the floppy disk.  If no file is named then the data is taken from the standard input. 

@{i}Samdiskread@{ui} and @{i}samdiskwrite@{ui} are implemented by the same program; which function is performed depends only upon whether the basename of the program contains the letter w. 


@endnode

@node sect3 "See Also"
samtools(1), samread(1), samwrite(1).  
@endnode
